            "content": "{\n  \"files\": [\n    {\n      \"repo\": \"api--v0.32.0\",\n      \"path\": \"apps/v1/types.go\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"repo\": \"client-go--v0.32.0\",\n      \"path\": \"examples/create-update-delete-deployment/main.go\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"repo\": \"client-go--v0.32.0\",\n      \"path\": \"examples/create-update-delete-deployment/README.md\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"repo\": \"client-go--v0.32.0\",\n      \"path\": \"README.md\"\n    }\n  ],\n  \"symbols\": [\n    {\n      \"repo\": \"api--v0.32.0\",\n      \"path\": \"apps/v1/types.go\",\n      \"symbol\": \"Deployment\"\n    }\n  ],\n  \"chain\": [\n    {\n      \"repo\": \"client-go--v0.32.0\",\n      \"path\": \"examples/create-update-delete-deployment/main.go\",\n      \"symbol\": \"main\"\n    }\n  ],\n  \"text\": \"The canonical patterns for deploying new services in Kubernetes are found across multiple repositories:\\n\\n1. **API Type Definition**: The authoritative `Deployment` struct is defined in the `api--v0.32.0` repository (kubernetes/api), specifically at `apps/v1/types.go` starting at line 359. This defines the core API structure: `type Deployment struct` which includes TypeMeta, ObjectMeta, Spec, and Status fields.\\n\\n2. **Client-side Code Pattern**: The canonical Go code example demonstrating how to create a Deployment using the client library is located in `client-go--v0.32.0/examples/create-update-delete-deployment/main.go`. This example shows the complete lifecycle:\\n   - **Create**: Using `deploymentsClient.Create(context.TODO(), deployment, metav1.CreateOptions{})`\\n   - **Update**: Using `retry.RetryOnConflict()` with `deploymentsClient.Update()` for handling conflicts\\n   - **List**: Using `deploymentsClient.List(context.TODO(), metav1.ListOptions{})`\\n   - **Delete**: Using `deploymentsClient.Delete()` with PropagationPolicy foreground deletion\\n\\n3. **Developer Documentation**: \\n   - The primary documentation is at `client-go--v0.32.0/examples/create-update-delete-deployment/README.md`, which explains the deployment workflow and how to run the example\\n   - The main `client-go--v0.32.0/README.md` provides overall client library documentation and explains that code development occurs in `kubernetes/kubernetes/staging/src/k8s.io/api` and `kubernetes/kubernetes/staging/src/k8s.io/client-go`\\n\\nKey pattern insight: The Deployment struct in the API repo is the single source of truth, and the client-go example demonstrates the recommended pattern of using `retry.RetryOnConflict()` when updating to handle concurrent modifications, which is the canonical approach for managing Kubernetes resources safely.\"\n}\n",
